@Steve L 

I found your first post above uncharacteristically snarky for you. I mean, yeah, many of us will not spot the theme (I know I didn't), but do you really think so little of your fellow solvers as to presume we will not understand how the theme worked having read the column? That can't be the case, can it? You're not that sort of guy.

If a Thursday is so easy you can ignore the theme and still solve it very quickly ( like I did), it really is on the puzzle, not the solver. I'm not criticizing the constructor BTW - maybe she submitted it for another day of the week, or maybe the editors made some changes to the original grid. Still, this was not a proper Thursday puzzle for me and I'm not the one who made it so.

